210	#### `packages/plugins/fabricator/src/fabricator.ts` — `EngineRunContext`
211	
212	```typescript
213	import type { BlockRecord } from '@shardworks/spider-apparatus';
214	
215	export interface EngineRunContext {
216	  engineId: string;
217	  upstream: Record<string, unknown>;
218	  /** Present when this engine was previously blocked and has been restarted. Advisory — do not depend on for correctness. */
219	  priorBlock?: BlockRecord;
220	}
221	```
222	
223	Note: This creates a type-level import from spider-apparatus into fabricator-apparatus. If this introduces a circular dependency (spider depends on fabricator, fabricator imports a type from spider), the `BlockRecord` interface must instead be duplicated in fabricator or moved to a shared types package. Check the package dependency graph at build time. If circular, define `BlockRecord` inline in the `EngineRunContext` type:
224	
225	```typescript
226	export interface EngineRunContext {
227	  engineId: string;
228	  upstream: Record<string, unknown>;
229	  priorBlock?: {
230	    type: string;
231	    condition: unknown;
232	    blockedAt: string;
233	    message?: string;
234	    lastCheckedAt?: string;
235	  };
236	}
237	```
238	
239	This avoids the cross-package import while maintaining the same shape. The Spider populates this field from its own `BlockRecord` value.
240	
241	### Behavior
242	
243	#### Block Type Registry (`packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.ts`)
244	
245	**Type guard:**
246	
247	```typescript
248	function isBlockType(value: unknown): value is BlockType {
249	  return (
250	    typeof value === 'object' &&
251	    value !== null &&
252	    typeof (value as Record<string, unknown>).id === 'string' &&
253	    typeof (value as Record<string, unknown>).check === 'function'
254	  );
255	}
256	```
257	
258	Checks `id` (string) and `check` (function) — the two required fields. Mirrors `isEngineDesign()`.
259	
260	**BlockTypeRegistry class:**
261	
262	Follow the exact same pattern as `EngineRegistry` in `packages/plugins/fabricator/src/fabricator.ts`:
263	
264	```typescript
265	class BlockTypeRegistry {
266	  private readonly types = new Map<string, BlockType>();
267	
268	  register(plugin: LoadedPlugin): void {
269	    if (isLoadedKit(plugin)) {
270	      this.registerFromKit(plugin.kit);
271	    } else if (isLoadedApparatus(plugin)) {
272	      if (plugin.apparatus.supportKit) {
273	        this.registerFromKit(plugin.apparatus.supportKit);
274	      }
275	    }
276	  }
277	
278	  private registerFromKit(kit: Record<string, unknown>): void {
279	    const raw = kit.blockTypes;
280	    if (typeof raw !== 'object' || raw === null) return;
281	    for (const value of Object.values(raw as Record<string, unknown>)) {
282	      if (isBlockType(value)) {
283	        this.types.set(value.id, value);
284	      }
285	    }
286	  }
287	
288	  get(id: string): BlockType | undefined {
289	    return this.types.get(id);
290	  }
291	}
292	```
