343	#### `isRigBlocked` Helper
344	
345	```typescript
346	function isRigBlocked(engines: EngineInstance[]): boolean {
347	  const hasRunning = engines.some((e) => e.status === 'running');
348	  if (hasRunning) return false;
349	  const hasBlocked = engines.some((e) => e.status === 'blocked');
350	  if (!hasBlocked) return false;
351	  return findRunnableEngine({ engines } as RigDoc) === null;
352	}
353	```
354	
355	Condition: no engine `running`, no engine runnable (pending with all upstream completed), at least one engine `blocked`. `findRunnableEngine` already encodes the "runnable" check.
356	
357	**Call sites:**
358	
359	- `tryRun()` — after engine transitions to `blocked`, call `isRigBlocked()` to determine whether rig enters `blocked`.
360	- `tryCollect()` — after a running engine completes, check `isRigBlocked()` on remaining engines. If true, set rig to `blocked` instead of leaving at `running`.
361	- `tryCheckBlocked()` — after unblocking an engine, the rig should be restored to `running` (this is always done, since blocked rigs don't have runnable engines by definition).
362	
363	**`tryCollect()` modification:** After an engine is collected as `completed`, the existing code checks `allCompleted`. Add an additional branch: if not all completed, check `isRigBlocked(updatedEngines)`. If true, set rig status to `blocked` and return `{ action: 'rig-blocked', rigId, writId }`.
